betterquesting:10.desc:8: Since there are no ores left in the world you will need to find other ways to obtain resources.  Luckily iron was commonly used for building supports.  You should be able to find some and melt it down in the smeltery.
Now that you have lava you can power the large smeltery
Obsidian can be obtained by combining lava and water in the smeltery

Aluminium oxide can be obtained by dissolving igneous rock in the chemical dissolver.  Aluminium oxide can be further refined down into aluminium which can then be used in the chemical combiner to make aluminium ingots
Copper can be made by using mineral salts in the chemical dissolver.  You can then use the chemical combiner to create a copper ingot.
Traces of gold ore can be found in the nether.  Alternatively you can dissolve netherrack to extract gold and use it in the chemical combiner to make an ingot.

Lead Iodide can be created by dissolving yellow dye in a chemical dissolver.  Lead Iodide can be further refined into lead in the chemical dissolver.  Lead can then be used to make lead ingot in a chemical combiner.
Can be made in the smeltery by combining copper and aluminum
Diamond can be made in the chemical combiner using carbon
A meteorite can be found with the use of a meteorite compass.
An energetic Infuser can be used to charge certus quartz
Basics to get you up and running
